parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: All safety system alerts appear on the dashboard
including those related to power steering

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause difficulty steering the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: causing difficulty manually steering the vehicle
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause reduced brake performance, increasing the risk of accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake system warning lights appear on the dashboard
and screeching or extreme noise from the rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the wireless charger can cause inconvenience and frustration for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: Wireless charger pad does not charge phone
even when the car is parked and sitting still.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission and engine can cause unexpected behavior, such as jerking or revving, which can be unsettling and potentially dangerous.
symptoms: Vehicle jerks when coming to a stop
loud thud noise when switching gears
and engine revs to 7000rpm even when driving at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of acceleration, jerking, and stalling, which can lead to accidents, especially on high-speed roads. It can also cause anxiety and uncertainty for the driver.
symptoms: vehicle won't accelerate past a few miles per hour
jerking or revving to high RPMs

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The whining/whistling noise can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to transmission failure, which can cause loss of acceleration, jerking, and stalling, and increase the risk of accidents.
Transmission fluid/oil leaks can cause damage to the transmission and other components, leading to premature wear and potentially catastrophic failure, which can cause accidents.
symptoms: noise while shifting from Park to Reverse to Drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, scattering of glass shards, and potentially distract the driver, leading to accidents or injuries. The shattered glass can also pose a risk to occupants and other vehicles nearby.
symptoms: glass shards scattered inside and outside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of the automatic braking system can cause sudden and unexpected stops, which can lead to accidents, rear-end collisions, or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and unexpectedly brakes or slows down without any obstacles or pedestrians in front of it
often at high speeds or in busy intersections
and may not respond to accelerator input.
